'''Line regulation''' is the ability to maintain a constant output voltage level on the output channel of a [[power supply]] despite changes to the input voltage level.
:<math>\text{Regulation} = \frac{\Delta V_\text{out}}{\Delta V_\text{in}} \cdot 100\%</math>
