The '''Yale Program on Climate Change Communication''' ('''YPCCC''') is a research center within the School of Forestry and Environmental Studies at [[Yale University]] that conducts scientific research on public [[climate change]] knowledge, attitudes, policy preferences, and behavior at the global, national, and local scales. It grew out of a conference held in Aspen, Colorado in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://climatecommunication.yale.edu/about/the-program/|title=About the Program|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Yale Program on Climate Change Communication|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>
==General== As of 2017 the program was led by [[Anthony Leiserowitz]], and it put out a daily 90 second audio program carried by around 350 radio stations, articles in the media, and a series of videos published monthly, and provided training to help television [[Weather_forecasting#Broadcasts|weather presenters]] and reporters discuss climate change.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Abraham |first1=John |title=Great climate science communication from Yale Climate Connections |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/climate-consensus-97-per-cent/2017/aug/14/great-cliate-science-communication-from-yale-climate-connections |work=the Guardian |date=14 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref>
In 2017 the program was given a "Friend of the Planet" award by the [[National Center for Science Education]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Press release: Friend of Darwin and Friend of the Planet awards for 2017 |url=https://ncse.com/news/2017/02/friend-darwin-friend-planet-awards-2017-0018458 |work=NCSE |date=13 February 2017 |language=en}}</ref> In 2018, Leiserowitz and YPCCC researchers received the Warren J. Mitofsky Innovators Award, given by the American Association for Public Opinion Research. The award recognized "a new statistical method to downscale national public opinion estimates using multiple regression and post stratification (MPR) survey data collection methodology."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aapor.org/Conference-Events/Awards/Award-Winners.aspx|title=Award Winners|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
